# PGC-213 repro: pipeline a slow, uncacheable statement immediately before a
# cacheable SELECT that is already a cache hit. Both simple-query messages are
# sent before any response is read, so pgcache reads the cacheable query while
# the uncacheable DO is still running on origin.
#
# Correct ordering: the DO's response (CommandComplete, no DataRow) must reach
# the client before the cache hit's DataRow. The bug lets the worker write the
# cache response directly to the socket ahead of the in-flight origin response.
'Q'	"DO $$ BEGIN PERFORM pg_sleep(0.3); END $$"
'Q'	"SELECT id, name FROM proto_pipeline WHERE id = 1"
'Y'
'Y'
'X'
